>twokinds even worth reading?
Yes and No. It will really depend on you personally. The art & story start out rough, like REALLY rough. The art eventually gets not just better but amazing. So, a Yes because you need to know the story (for all its flaws) to fully enjoy the art & characters & jokes & bantz. But, a No if you don't think you can enjoy a flawed gem just for what it is. The story had much more potential than Tom has managed to give it. So far. And, it updates slowly.
